 https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/work-hard/
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id="work-hard"&gt;Work hard&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Every mathematician worthy of the name has experienced … the state of lucid exaltation in which one thought succeeds another as if miraculously… this feeling may last for hours at a time, even for days. Once you have experienced it, you are eager to repeat it but unable to do it at will, unless perhaps by dogged work…&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Weil"&gt;André Weil&lt;/a&gt;, “The Apprenticeship of a Mathematician”)&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The 80-hour Myth</title><link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-80-hour-myth/</link><pubDate>Tue, 29 Nov 2005 12:56:48 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-80-hour-myth/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/the-80-hour-myth.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
